        <span class="instructions">Part 1:</span>
        <p class="instructions2">God will lead me!</p>
        <p>I need God’s Holy Spirit to reveal His vision and individual mission for my life. God speaks to us using the Holy Spirit through our reading and hearing teachings on the Bible, prayer with Him, circumstances in our lives, the church (the body of other believers in Christ), and the words and actions of others in our lives to reveal Himself, His purposes, and His ways. These things need to be revealed to us before we can consider whether we are even pursuing the right things in our lives or whether we are just wasting our time. It may be that our next job offer (from a worldly perspective) is totally wrong as a career choice; however, from His perspective, it may be the perfect “tent-making” opportunity to equip us for His next assignment in our lives. We should willingly accept any job that is clearly from God’s hand. We should also recognize that all jobs are temporary (temporal) and the “job assignment search” (seeking and following God’s will) is continuous (eternal). Our ultimate loyalty must always be to the Father and not to any job, company, or career path.</p>
        <p>The ultimate purpose of our work and career path will always be connected in some way to understanding and being more like Christ, bringing all glory to the Father, and making disciples for Christ in the power of the Holy Spirit.</p>
        <p><i>“For by grace you have been saved through faith; and this not from yourselves, it is the gift of God; not as a result of works, so that no one may boast. For we are His workmanship, created in Christ Jesus for good works, which God prepared beforehand so that we would walk in them.”</i> <b>(Ephesians 2:8-10 NASB)</b></p>
        <p>Let us begin this spiritual journey together with Him, do all that we can, and then trust Him fully for the results!</p>
