        <span class="instructions">Part 2:</span>
        <p>The following has been paraphrased from <i>The Seven Seasons of the Man in the Mirror</i> by Patrick Morley:</p>
        <p class="instructions2">How to be successful in the Lord:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Depend on God’s resources, not just your own. – Courage is not the absence of fear, but instead, a willingness to trust God anyways in the presence of fear.</li>
            <br />
            <li>Do everything you do in the name of the Lord! – So closely identify everything you do with God, so that before men can prevail against you, they must first prevail against God Himself.</li>
            <br />
            <li>Take personal responsibility for your own life! – Aggressively follow-up with whatever God reveals for you to do, and be thankful for whatever God decides that you should do, and whatever the resulting outcome.</li>
            <br />
            <li>God is not calling you to be successful; instead, He is calling for you to be faithful to Him!</li>
            <br />
            <li>Fix your eyes on Jesus, run your race with perseverance, and do not grow weary or lose heart!</li>
            <br />
            <li>Take risks, depend on God, take personal responsibility for your actions, and expect opposition. – The great secret of contentment is not getting what you want, but instead, wanting what you get.</li>
            <br />
            <li>No amount of success at work will compensate for failure at home. True success is to satisfy God’s calling for our lives, not our ambitions!</li>
            <br />
            <li><b>A truly successful person is one of courage, wisdom, commitment, and balance! (Morley, 1995)</b></li>
        </ul>
        <p><b><u>Reference:</u></b></p>
        <p>Morley, P. (1995). <i>The Seven Seasons of the Man in the Mirror</i>. Grand Rapids, MI: Zondervan.</p>
